WEBVTT

00:19.040 --> 00:20.000
Turn on the light.

00:28.640 --> 00:30.800
-Is anyone in there?
-The paramedic.

00:31.160 --> 00:31.920
Okay wait a minute

00:33.480 --> 00:34.240
What do you have there?

00:34.360 --> 00:35.280
A thirty-five year old.

00:35.400 --> 00:37.280
He was transported
with a ruptured appendix.

00:37.400 --> 00:38.360
Early sepsis.

00:38.480 --> 00:39.960
Blunt injuries to the
head, chest and abdomen.

00:40.080 --> 00:41.040
Over with him now.

00:41.880 --> 00:43.400
-Who is this?
-The pilot.

00:43.800 --> 00:44.400
How is she doing?

00:44.520 --> 00:46.040
Serious facial
injury, neck bleeding.

00:46.160 --> 00:47.360
Cannot intubate because
of blood in the mouth.

00:47.480 --> 00:48.640
The car will explode.

00:57.800 --> 01:00.320
As a basketball team doctor,
I take care of the injuries.

01:00.440 --> 01:03.160
Everything from
blisters to broken bones.

01:04.120 --> 01:05.280
Great.  Sports.

01:06.000 --> 01:07.720
Aren't you impressed
with the talent it takes?

01:07.840 --> 01:09.080
Basketball is not my thing.

01:09.440 --> 01:12.160
But if Tony Hawk gets
the 900 degree, I'll be there.

01:12.520 --> 01:14.120
Do you really want this job?

01:14.640 --> 01:16.520
Are you kidding?  It
looks great on the résumé.

01:16.840 --> 01:18.520
And there is extra money.

01:18.640 --> 01:21.040
If you're that interested,
you better listen.

01:21.280 --> 01:23.440
If you are one of those interns

01:23.560 --> 01:24.920
who will help me, you will too.

01:25.040 --> 01:28.440
And you also get one
of these cool jackets.

01:29.280 --> 01:30.920
It says "team doctor
assistant" on it.

01:33.440 --> 01:34.480
Who is he talking to?

01:34.960 --> 01:36.880
With the director
of Waverly Athletic.

01:37.200 --> 01:39.360
Angus showing him around?
How do they know each other?

01:39.920 --> 01:42.520
It must have been his dad.
Incomprehensible.

01:43.000 --> 01:44.280
Do you have any questions
about the program?

01:44.400 --> 01:45.560
Forgiveness.  Rorish.

01:46.000 --> 01:47.680
This is Willis.
You have to cut that short.

01:47.800 --> 01:48.920
I was on the way in the emergency vehicle.

01:49.040 --> 01:50.880
Yet again?  You need a hobby.

01:51.240 --> 01:53.560
Pot on lid.
I'm sending you a disaster.

01:54.000 --> 01:55.000
What a disaster?

01:55.120 --> 01:57.080
One patient was
evacuated from a cruise.

01:57.200 --> 01:59.800
The helicopter crashed.
I'm sending you two by bus.

02:00.040 --> 02:00.960
We will be prepared.

02:01.880 --> 02:02.560
Doc!

02:02.680 --> 02:04.520
We are ready!  He is conscious!

02:08.720 --> 02:09.759
What's your name?

02:10.000 --> 02:12.160
Brad.  Brad Souza.
I'm the medic on board.

02:12.840 --> 02:15.760
-Is my patient alive?
-He's on his way to the Angels.

02:16.400 --> 02:17.920
What about my pilot, Debbie?

02:18.400 --> 02:20.600
I don't know how,
but she saved us...

02:20.720 --> 02:22.520
I'm worried about
you, understand?

02:22.760 --> 02:24.240
It's pretty stuck there.

02:25.000 --> 02:26.160
The fire flares up again!

02:28.400 --> 02:30.200
What kind of offensive
strategy do you have in mind?

02:30.480 --> 02:33.240
-Motion or Triple Post?
-The one my team wins.

02:33.640 --> 02:35.560
You have no idea
about basketball, do you?

02:35.680 --> 02:37.680
We don't play for the
team when we get the job.

02:38.280 --> 02:39.840
We'll be doctors.
I think I can do it.

02:40.000 --> 02:41.920
Leighton, Savetti,
talk about sports later.

02:42.080 --> 02:43.320
You need to focus on this.

02:43.440 --> 02:45.200
These are the first two victims
of the rescue helicopter crash.

02:52.160 --> 02:54.200
Thirty-five year old
with a ruptured appendix.

02:54.320 --> 02:57.000
Blunt injuries to the
head, chest and abdomen.

02:57.120 --> 03:00.480
He is hypotensive and hypoxic,
blood pressure is 74 to 46.

03:00.600 --> 03:03.120
Can I have my cell phone?
I have to call my wife.

03:03.240 --> 03:05.040
I left her and my 8
year old on the boat.

03:05.240 --> 03:07.720
Sir, you can call her
when we've stabilized you.

03:07.840 --> 03:10.280
A forty year old, blood
pressure is at 90 to 52.

03:10.400 --> 03:11.360
Her name is Debbie.

03:11.480 --> 03:14.000
Serious facial injuries,
post nasal intubation on site.

03:14.120 --> 03:15.000
I see.

03:15.120 --> 03:16.640
The oxygen saturation
drops, it is around 85.

03:16.760 --> 03:17.760
Let's take them to
the Center Stage.

03:17.880 --> 03:19.680
All right, Debbie, we have you.
Where is Dr.  Willis?

03:19.800 --> 03:20.920
Still on site.

03:31.760 --> 03:33.040
Okay, please.

03:38.160 --> 03:39.480
It is firmly fused
with the seat.

03:42.240 --> 03:43.560
Fine, I'll cut out his seat.

03:43.680 --> 03:45.080
We take the whole thing with us.

03:45.440 --> 03:47.360
All right?  Come on!

03:47.840 --> 03:49.200
What's happening?  What are you doing?

03:50.400 --> 03:51.760
We'll get you out of here.

03:52.640 --> 03:54.960
I'll give you some morphine.
That will help.

03:56.080 --> 03:59.200
What about Rowan?
The patient?  His family?

03:59.320 --> 04:01.160
I promised him that
he would see her again.

04:01.280 --> 04:02.280
You will keep your promise.

04:03.920 --> 04:05.520
The thing is leaking fuel.

04:06.200 --> 04:07.240
Fast.

04:09.640 --> 04:11.360
Fast fast.

04:24.160 --> 04:25.520
The lungs are free.

04:25.640 --> 04:27.320
But ventilation becomes difficult.
The saturation is low.

04:27.440 --> 04:28.920
Your inner tracheal tube
may have slipped out of place.

04:30.360 --> 04:34.520
Your jaw is dislocated.
He presses the breathing tube shut.

04:34.680 --> 04:36.760
Put it on so it doesn't
bite your thumb off.

04:38.560 --> 04:40.240
The saturation is down to 72%.

04:44.120 --> 04:46.160
Okay, we can do it, Debbie.

04:47.840 --> 04:50.560
Male, in his forties, 3rd
degree burn on his back.

04:50.680 --> 04:52.600
He was fused with the
seat and is the medic.

04:52.720 --> 04:53.720
Calls the combustion ITS.

04:53.840 --> 04:55.440
We couldn't separate
him from the chair on site.

04:55.560 --> 04:56.920
We have to operate it slowly.

04:57.040 --> 04:58.960
Very slowly.
Let's stabilize it.

05:00.120 --> 05:01.840
Why do you always attract anger?

05:02.040 --> 05:03.800
Good question.  How is she doing?

05:03.920 --> 05:06.160
-Stable enough for the operating room.
-I'll bring them up myself.

05:06.280 --> 05:07.240
Got it.

05:08.560 --> 05:10.160
Diffuse pressure sensitivity
and defense tension.

05:11.320 --> 05:12.520
The belly is full of blood.

05:13.200 --> 05:14.680
He has to go to the operating room.  Fast!

05:14.800 --> 05:16.280
Arms are burned.
I can't get access.

05:16.400 --> 05:17.400
He needs an esophagojejunostomy.

05:17.520 --> 05:18.720
We'll take care of you, Brad.

05:19.680 --> 05:20.600
-Do you know him?
-Yes.

05:20.720 --> 05:23.360
The two have been flying
patients to us for years.

05:23.480 --> 05:24.560
He has breathing problems.

05:24.680 --> 05:26.680
The burns extend from
the back to the chest

05:27.400 --> 05:28.360
and prevent breathing.

05:28.960 --> 05:30.400
He cannot dilate his lungs.

05:31.240 --> 05:32.440
-Fascia split.
-Yes.

05:32.600 --> 05:34.520
Dr.  Kean, we need
to separate the chair

05:34.640 --> 05:36.120
from the back and
cut through the burns.

05:36.240 --> 05:37.520
To do this, he has to go to the operating room.

05:37.640 --> 05:39.120
Risa, please call
Incineration ITS.

05:39.240 --> 05:40.280
They are already on their way.

05:42.760 --> 05:45.040
The saturation is down to 74.
Shall we intubate him?

05:45.320 --> 05:46.280
That won't help.

05:46.400 --> 05:48.240
We have to remove the
chair or it will suffocate.

05:48.360 --> 05:50.040
So much too
"slowly and carefully".

05:53.080 --> 05:53.880
What do we have here?

05:54.000 --> 05:56.240
Debbie, the helicopter pilot,
collapsed in the elevator.

06:00.800 --> 06:04.240
Hamman sign.  Air loss.
We have to open it!

06:05.400 --> 06:07.120
Pulse oximetry says 64%.

06:07.280 --> 06:09.800
You take off the
chair, I open my chest.

06:10.000 --> 06:12.640
-I need betadine.
-I can hardly ventilate him.

06:12.760 --> 06:14.720
-You need to work faster.
-He collapses.

06:14.840 --> 06:18.400
Come on, Brad.  Stay with us.
We're almost there.

06:18.520 --> 06:20.160
-He will be separated soon.
-Scalpel.

06:20.280 --> 06:21.880
On my side too.  Let's pull.

06:22.040 --> 06:24.280
One two Three.

06:24.400 --> 06:25.760
I've reached the subcutis.

06:34.880 --> 06:35.960
The values ​​improve.

06:36.480 --> 06:37.560
The pulse is strong.

06:37.880 --> 06:39.080
He's not over the hill yet.

06:39.640 --> 06:41.400
Let's put it on and take
it to the incineration ITS.

06:47.200 --> 06:48.800
Your daughter threw
a stapler at my son!

06:48.920 --> 06:51.600
-Is she crazy or what?
-No she is not.

06:51.720 --> 06:54.120
Your son laughed at
your daughter's clothes.

06:54.240 --> 06:55.240
He annoyed her.

06:55.360 --> 06:57.840
Okay, but who ended
up in the hospital?

06:57.960 --> 07:00.400
-Your daughter belongs in custody!
- Relax, sir.

07:00.520 --> 07:02.600
Take care of yourself.
Just sew the wound up.

07:02.720 --> 07:04.360
-Dad...
-All right, son.  I will solve that.

07:04.480 --> 07:07.840
No, I mean my head
is about to explode.

07:07.960 --> 07:10.640
And my eye is totally blurry.

07:10.760 --> 07:13.640
-I beg your pardon?  What's happening?
-I'm going to take a closer look.

07:13.760 --> 07:16.240
-That hurts?
-Yes, insane.

07:16.360 --> 07:17.920
What's happening?
Talk to me right away!

07:18.040 --> 07:19.840
It might not be anything,
but we need to do a CT.

07:22.680 --> 07:23.640
We will pay for that!

07:23.760 --> 07:25.440
-Mom can we go?
-April, please...

07:25.560 --> 07:26.640
Go, I'm serious.

07:26.760 --> 07:28.240
No, it's expensive.

07:28.360 --> 07:31.400
Medical bills are expensive,
I'll sue you for everything.

07:31.520 --> 07:34.120
Dr.  Dixon, are
you under control?

07:34.240 --> 07:36.080
-I try it.
-Who are you?

07:37.160 --> 07:39.320
The head of the emergency
room and chief of surgery.

07:43.160 --> 07:44.280
Hey buddy.

07:45.880 --> 07:48.000
What does this patient
need, Dr.  Dixon?

07:48.160 --> 07:49.920
A CT scan of the brain and eye socket.

07:50.080 --> 07:51.320
Make that happen.

08:02.240 --> 08:03.520
- Doctor Rorish.
-Thank you.

08:07.680 --> 08:10.720
-Debbie didn't make it.
-I am sorry.

08:12.400 --> 08:14.760
She was the first
female pilot I ever met.

08:16.680 --> 08:18.000
I have to call her parents.

08:20.200 --> 08:21.800
What do you want to do with Brad?

08:21.960 --> 08:23.760
I'd like to tell him
if you don't mind.

08:25.480 --> 08:27.040
You are practically part of the family.

08:33.880 --> 08:35.760
That should help with the pain.

08:37.200 --> 08:39.039
We spoke to the surgeons.

08:39.600 --> 08:40.919
The good news:
the appendix is ​​out.

08:41.039 --> 08:42.000
And the bad one?

08:42.400 --> 08:45.400
You have a serious
stomach injury from the crash.

08:45.720 --> 08:47.680
We had to remove a
long piece of your bowel.

08:47.800 --> 08:48.840
Oh my God.

08:49.160 --> 08:50.400
We are watching
you carefully, but you

08:50.520 --> 08:53.320
should know that
complications can arise.

08:53.440 --> 08:57.120
I can't tell my wife that,
she worries too much.

08:58.920 --> 09:01.920
Rowan, thank goodness.
Are you all right?

09:03.440 --> 09:05.080
Yes sweetheart.  I am fine.

09:05.640 --> 09:07.800
My appendix was
removed, but I'm fine.

09:09.240 --> 09:10.160
Is jason with you

09:11.720 --> 09:13.440
Dad, when are you coming back?

09:13.640 --> 09:17.640
Not soon, buddy.
But I am taken care of.

09:19.200 --> 09:21.600
Hey, don't you want to be a doctor?

09:22.240 --> 09:25.520
How about I get you
a fancy stethoscope?

09:25.640 --> 09:26.720
This works out?

09:29.600 --> 09:31.160
Hey, give me one more mommy.

09:31.880 --> 09:34.360
How much did you give him
He should be in more pain.

09:34.480 --> 09:35.480
One milligram of Dilaudid.

09:35.600 --> 09:37.640
Intravenous?  Do you want
to lower his blood pressure?

09:37.760 --> 09:38.520
He's fresh out of the operating room.

09:38.640 --> 09:40.160
What is your problem?
His blood pressure is good.

09:40.280 --> 09:43.160
True, but he might still
have drugs in his blood.

09:43.280 --> 09:44.920
His D-dimer is increased,
could be an embolism.

09:45.040 --> 09:46.600
And you could have stray herpes,

09:46.720 --> 09:47.960
but I guess you don't have one.

09:48.640 --> 09:50.000
What's wrong with you?

09:50.880 --> 09:52.760
How do you know the
head of sport at Waverly?

09:53.080 --> 09:54.080
Oh my God.

09:54.480 --> 09:55.440
Through your dad, right?

09:55.560 --> 09:57.800
I can not believe that.
This is what this is about

09:58.160 --> 09:59.960
I have the same right
to the job as you do.

10:00.080 --> 10:03.320
I had to fight for
everything I achieved in life.

10:04.080 --> 10:05.880
-You never fought.
-What are you saying?

10:06.000 --> 10:08.120
Your dad.  You've
always had it easy

10:08.240 --> 10:09.520
in life and I've
always had it difficult.

10:09.640 --> 10:11.400
Hey is there a problem?

10:13.320 --> 10:15.040
-No.
-No.

10:15.760 --> 10:17.320
Then stop arguing
in front of the patient.

10:17.640 --> 10:19.800
Not just in front of the patient.

10:22.880 --> 10:25.120
May I have one of
these stethoscopes?

10:27.040 --> 10:28.160
I see what I can do

10:29.320 --> 10:30.680
-No no.
-One two Three.

10:32.080 --> 10:34.080
Girls between 8 and 10
found alone in the mall.

10:34.240 --> 10:37.080
Very upset.
Wheezing and slight hypoxia.

10:37.200 --> 10:38.680
Your oxygen saturation
continues to decrease.

10:42.320 --> 10:43.600
Well i'm going

10:43.880 --> 10:47.080
Take it easy.
Head injuries or fever?

10:47.200 --> 10:49.160
No, the police are looking
for their parents right now.

10:49.920 --> 10:51.360
You should fix them four times.

10:51.480 --> 10:52.640
What's going on here?

10:53.160 --> 10:54.760
We won't fix a child fourfold!

10:58.800 --> 10:59.920
Oxygen is at 86%.

11:00.040 --> 11:01.600
Has she already eaten
or drank something?

11:01.720 --> 11:02.800
-Does she have any medication?
-No.

11:04.400 --> 11:07.560
Hey where are your parents

11:12.200 --> 11:13.280
You don't have to be afraid.

11:15.840 --> 11:18.080
We put the mask
on you so that you...

11:23.240 --> 11:25.120
I have to put the mask
on you so that you...

11:27.600 --> 11:29.480
She can hear us,
she just doesn't react.

11:30.760 --> 11:32.600
Zoe!  Zoe?  Mommy's here baby

11:33.280 --> 11:35.720
Is she OK?  I lost
her.  She ran away.

11:36.800 --> 11:38.600
-I can calm you down.
-OK.

11:38.840 --> 11:41.520
She has to be ventilated.
Can you put it on her?

11:41.640 --> 11:42.360
Thank you.

11:42.920 --> 11:45.200
She is autistic.  She doesn't
get along well with strangers.

11:47.840 --> 11:51.080
-Just put them on...
-Don't worry, I know that.

11:51.200 --> 11:52.760
It's okay.  So...

11:54.440 --> 11:57.040
She must have pneumonia.
It would be the 4th time this year.

11:57.960 --> 11:59.320
She has asthma attacks in a panic.

12:00.240 --> 12:01.640
Have they been tested
for sickle cell anemia?

12:01.760 --> 12:03.680
Naturally.  She doesn't have it.

12:04.360 --> 12:09.840
What is the distance
from L.A. to Dallas?

12:09.960 --> 12:13.720
The distance between L.A.
and Dallas is...

12:13.840 --> 12:14.560
1040 nautical miles.

12:14.680 --> 12:18.720
She is talking on the
cell phone.  She repeats

12:18.840 --> 12:20.880
what's on TV and sometimes
with her stuffed animals.

12:22.640 --> 12:24.000
But she never speaks to me.

12:25.200 --> 12:30.120
She is 9 and never said a
word to me, not even "Mommy".

12:32.080 --> 12:34.440
One two Three...

12:34.600 --> 12:36.880
Oh god no  She counts
when she is in pain.

12:37.000 --> 12:38.000
Where does it hurt?

12:38.120 --> 12:39.600
No idea.
It points to several places.

12:39.840 --> 12:41.320
But when it radiates
or comes in waves...

12:41.440 --> 12:43.160
I do not know.  It just counts.

12:43.720 --> 12:47.880
-OK.
-...two three four...

13:04.720 --> 13:06.040
How is she doing?

13:07.680 --> 13:09.520
I saw that you
could ventilate her.

13:10.520 --> 13:11.880
And she is so strong.

13:13.800 --> 13:14.760
-Brad...
-I know her.

13:14.880 --> 13:17.360
She really wants to
work again, like me.

13:19.360 --> 13:20.320
Brad.

13:24.400 --> 13:27.240
I'm so sorry.
Debbie died in the operation.

13:35.000 --> 13:36.960
Everyone survives in my head.

13:38.000 --> 13:38.960
What do you mean by that?

13:42.240 --> 13:44.960
I'll throw it on your roof, fly
away and don't look back.

13:45.080 --> 13:46.120
In my thoughts...

13:48.520 --> 13:49.920
... live on.

13:51.840 --> 13:54.400
And what about the
patient, the appendix?

13:58.720 --> 13:59.680
It's stable.

14:01.800 --> 14:03.320
We do what we can.

14:04.080 --> 14:05.440
Will you keep me updated

14:07.040 --> 14:09.040
I promised him that he
would see the family again.

14:10.040 --> 14:12.480
I know.  We shouldn't
make promises.

14:13.920 --> 14:14.880
No.

14:16.240 --> 14:17.640
But we all do it.

14:20.440 --> 14:23.080
Dad, you have to come back.
You miss everything.

14:23.200 --> 14:27.120
I know buddy.  But
see what I found.

14:27.680 --> 14:30.320
I'll be able to hear
your heartbeat soon.

14:30.440 --> 14:33.720
In any case.  I promise.

14:35.280 --> 14:37.320
The CT shows bleeding behind the

14:37.440 --> 14:38.960
right eye, pressing
on the optic nerve.

14:39.200 --> 14:41.680
Why are you telling me that?
It is not my eye.

14:42.280 --> 14:43.840
True, but... I...

14:43.960 --> 14:46.040
I thought I could use some help.

14:46.520 --> 14:49.400
The boy is strong.  Maybe
you should talk to him.

14:49.520 --> 14:52.320
Dr.  Dixon, I pretend
I didn't hear this.

14:53.400 --> 14:55.800
Dealing with patients
is part of being a doctor.

14:56.080 --> 14:59.280
You either do the whole
job or nothing at all.

15:03.520 --> 15:06.120
I understand that as "No."

15:09.440 --> 15:12.040
Once implanted, the
neurostimulator sends

15:12.160 --> 15:16.120
electronics to different
areas of the brain

15:16.240 --> 15:18.360
and so relieve the symptoms
of Parkinson's disease.

15:19.480 --> 15:21.480
This is called a deep
brain stimulation surgery.

15:21.600 --> 15:24.120
Like a pacemaker for your brain.

15:26.800 --> 15:28.160
Yes, I heard about it.

15:29.440 --> 15:30.760
And have you done it before?

15:30.880 --> 15:34.080
A few times.
With different results.

15:38.680 --> 15:40.600
There is no guarantee
that it will work?

15:41.560 --> 15:43.560
Or that I will survive
the operation?

15:43.680 --> 15:45.880
There are risks, yes.

15:46.600 --> 15:49.960
You know that.  But it
seems promising for you.

15:50.080 --> 15:51.120
And that's rare.

15:51.360 --> 15:52.960
Not everyone is an option.

15:53.080 --> 15:55.080
Before the operation there
are first laboratory tests.

15:55.200 --> 15:56.640
We'll have it done today.

15:57.600 --> 15:59.400
-No.
-Rollie...

15:59.520 --> 16:00.640
The time window is tight.

16:00.760 --> 16:02.760
You are now a good candidate,
but I don't guarantee...

16:02.880 --> 16:03.960
-I am not ready.
-Rollie...

16:04.080 --> 16:05.240
No means no.

16:09.200 --> 16:11.560
Thank you.
I appreciate your time.

16:17.120 --> 16:18.760
-An operation?
-Yes.

16:18.920 --> 16:20.360
